# Roastproof — Extensible Codebase & Docs

Canonical detail lives in `CLAUDE.md`, `src/schemas.py`, and `docs/phases/`. Read those before inventing structure. This rule is the working contract for every change.

## Extensibility (keep the codebase editable)

- Prefer **small pure functions** + thin `__main__` / CLI wrappers. New features = new functions/modules, not mega-functions.
- Shared contracts go in `src/schemas.py` (Pydantic). Do not invent parallel dict shapes.
- All LLM calls go through `src/llm.py` only (G5). Never raw OpenAI clients elsewhere.
- Prompts live in `src/generation/prompts.py`. Corpus knowledge via `retrieve` / rulebook / norms — do not hardcode review wisdom in scattered strings.
- Generation Q&A persistence: sidecar `*.qa.yaml` via `qa_store.py`; do not stuff long Q&A history into intake YAML.
- Elicitation coverage is **dimension-precise** (`intake_coverage.py`). Never “any digit ⇒ covered” or silent round-1 converge with empty questions.
- Project eval must cite real critique `id=` when retrieval returns ids; `rule:` alone is not enough.
- Add/adjust **unit tests** for pure logic you touch (`tests/`). Mock LLM calls.

## Data & file map (do not invent paths)

| Path | Role |
|---|---|
| `data/raw/` | Frozen scraped snapshot (ingestion input) |
| `data/holdout/` | Eval-only — **only** `src/eval/` may read (G4) |
| `data/structured/threads.jsonl` | Phase 1 |
| `data/norms/` | Phase 2 norms |
| `data/knowledge/` + `data/chroma/` | Phase 3 rulebook + vectors |
| `logs/llm_calls.jsonl` | Every LLM call (G5) |
| `examples/*.yaml` + `*.qa.yaml` | Intake + elicitation sidecar |
| `out/` | Pipeline runs (PDF, content, suggestions, status) |
| `templates/jakes_resume.tex.j2` | Sole v1 resume template |
| `src/scraper/` | Standalone Discord utility — not a pipeline phase |

Pipeline flow: intake → elicit (sidecar) → generate (G1) → project_eval → render/pagefit → `out/`.

Hard guardrails G1–G5 always apply (no fabrication; PII sweep on ingest; cost control; holdout isolation; shared LLM logger).

## Docs hygiene (required)

After **every** working session that changes behavior or APIs:

1. Append a newest-first entry to `CHANGELOG.md` (files, why, results/metrics). Erfan uses it for commits.

After a **major** update (new phase substep, public CLI flags, schema fields users see, pipeline behavior change, or acceptance-criteria shift):

2. Update the matching `docs/phases/phase*.md` (status, acceptance, how-to).
3. Update `CLAUDE.md` when phase status, structure, schemas, or execution rules change.
4. Update `README.md` when user-facing setup, commands, or phase table drift from reality.

Do **not** edit user plan files under `.cursor/plans/` unless asked. Prefer editing code + the docs above.
